<div class="banner" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.3),rgba(0,0,0,0.3)), url(https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1497366811353-6870744d04b2?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2301&q=80);">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Meeting Minute</h1>
     <p>
      <span id="banner-typed-text"></span>
    </p>
<!--     <p>Simplifying the Hectic Schedule into Actionables</p> -->
    <div class="button-sign-up">
      <%= link_to "Sign Up", new_user_registration_path, class:"btn btn-ghost"%>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="box-heading no-flex">
    <h2 class="title-after-banner ml-3 mr-3">Change your daily meetings into automatically generated minutes, that you can check in a single place, add them to your calendar and attach to emails to send to all participants.</h2>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div id="carouselContent" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
        <div class="carousel-inner">
          <!-- 1st -->
            <div class="carousel-item active text-center p-4">
            <header class="wrapper header-home">
              <div class="half">
                <h1 class="full-width">Simplifying your busy schedule</h1>
                <img class="calendar" width="600" alt="calendar" src="https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_images/DayView-Blog_2.gif">
              </div>
              <div class="half">
                <div class="box">
                <h3>Meeting Minute</h3>
                  <p>A simple extension for your browser that is added to each Hangouts call.</p>
                  <p>Meeting Minute will sit in on the call and help you with notetaking, so that you can quickly follow up on the meeting and make sure youâ€™re on top of all the issues covered.</p>
                  <p>Meeting Minute will extract participants, help you summarize the topics covered & propose actionables of the meeting.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </header>
            </div>
            <!-- 2nd -->
          <div class="carousel-item text-center p-4">
             <header class="wrapper">
                <h1 class="full-width mb-3">meetingminute.io</h1>
                <div class="bannermeeting">
                  <%= image_tag "bannermeeting", width:1000%>
                </div>
            </header>
            </div>

            <div class="carousel-item text-center p-4">
             <header class="wrapper header-home">
              <div class="half">
                <h1 class="full-width">From meeting to minute</h1>
                <h1 class="full-width">(AI powered Meeting assistant)</h1>
                <%= image_tag "videocall_transparent", class: "carousel-image"%>
              </div>
              <div class="half">
                <div class="box">
                <h3 class="mx-auto">How it works</h3>
                  <p>Quickly identifies participants by matching the calendar to the users that joined the meeting.</p>
                  <p>Access to microphone & audio allows it to detect the conversation.</p>
                  <p>Access to the subtitle options being created by google allows it to access the speech translated into text.</p>
                  <p>By accessing the speech it can quickly transform phrases into quick cards and ask the user if it was a covered topic or an actionable.</p>
                  <p>5 minutes before the end it previews the meeting minute and asks the user for feedback, or if there is anything missing (suggestions of what might be missing are also available).</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </header>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselContent" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselContent" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>



